#Rats' Feast (#1085) - PARKED, REAL BUG MAPPED:
#The <prex> chooser on the resolution choice menus reads X from the POOL-DIFF
#fallback, not the chosen X: the cast sets setX on the stack instance, but by
#resolution the spell's card is the recreated graveyard instance (setX=-1), so
#prex = leftover pool = 0 and the exile chooser accepts nothing. Diagnostic: with
#{2} deliberately left floating the exile works perfectly (X read = 2).
#Same stale-instance family as the pay[[ residue. Engine item: propagate setX
#through zone-move recreation (MTGCardInstance::clone/copy), or have prex consult
#the spell rather than the card.
[INIT]
firstmain
[PLAYER1]
manapool:{2}{B}
hand:rats' feast
[PLAYER2]
graveyard:millstone,juggernaut,gold myr
[DO]
rats' feast
choice 2
goto firstmain
goto firstmain
choice 0
millstone
juggernaut
rats' feast
goto firstmain
goto firstmain
[ASSERT]
FIRSTMAIN
[PLAYER1]
graveyard:rats' feast
[PLAYER2]
graveyard:gold myr
exile:millstone,juggernaut
[END]
